[Similar Figures]
Two figures that are identical in shape but may be different in size.

[Similarity of Regular Polygons]
All regular polygons with the same number of sides are similar.

[Scale Factor]
The ratio of the corresponding side lengths of two similar figures.

[Area-Scale Factor Proportion]
Given two similar figures, the area of each figure is proportionate to its
scale factor, squared.

